{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "SB510", "title": "Pupil instruction: treatment of African Americans.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Pupilinstruction", "treatmentofAfricanAmericans"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law establishes the Instructional Quality Commission and requires the commission to, among other things, recommend curriculum frameworks to the State Board of Education. Existing law requires the commission, when the history-social science curriculum framework is next revised, on or after January 1, 2025, to consider providing for inclusion, in that curriculum framework, related evaluation criteria, and accompanying instructional materials, of instruction on the treatment and perspectives of Native Americans during the Spanish colonization of California and the Gold Rush Era.\n\nThis bill would require the commission, when the state board next revises the history-social science curriculum framework or adopts new instructional materials, on or after January 1, 2026, to consider including content on the historical, social, economic, and political contributions of African Americans during the Spanish colonization of California, the Gold Rush Era, and Antebellum, as provided."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "", "title": "Pupil instruction: racial disparities and historical injustices."}], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Introduced. Read first time. To Com. on RLS. for assignment. To print.", "date": "2025-02-19", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["introduction", "reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be acted upon on or after March 22.", "date": "2025-02-20", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on RLS.", "date": "2025-02-26", "organization_id": "~{\"classifi